{
    "post_id": 67620,
    "title": "שְׁלֹשׁ עֶשְׂרֵה בְּרִיתוֹת | Shlōsh Esréh Britōt — a Shiv'ata cycle for Musaf on the Shabbat of a bar mitsvah, by Isaac Gantwerk Mayer",
    "author": "Isaac Gantwerk Mayer",
    "coauthors": [
        {
            "name": "Isaac Gantwerk Mayer",
            "bio": "From a family of musicians, Isaac Gantwerk Mayer believes that creative art is one of the most powerful ways to get in touch with the divine. He composes music and poetry in Hebrew and English. (He also <a href=\"/index.php?user_ID=342\">translates</a> and <a href=\"/index.php?user_ID=820\">transcribes</a> Hebrew and Aramaic texts, adding <em>niqqud</em> and <em>t'amim</em> as needed.) Isaac runs a Jewish music transcription service, which will transcribe and set any Jewish music in any language, recorded or written. Contact his service on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pg/isaacgmayerjewishtranscription/\">Facebook</a> or via <a href=\"https://igmjewishcreativeworks.com/contact\">his music blog</a>.",
            "website": "https://igmjewishcreativeworks.com",
            "avatar": "https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/isaac-gantwerk-mayer-2021-e1674561264977-96x96.jpg",
            "profile_link": "https://opensiddur.org/profile/isaac-gantwerk-mayer"
        }
    ],
    "date": "2026-05-30",
    "last_updated": "2026-06-01",
    "excerpt": "A shiv'ata is a sevenfold blessing inserted into the Musaf service on Shabbat. This shiv'ata was written for use at a bar mitsvah. Each stanza begins with an example of thirteen as used in our tradition, followed by an alphabetical acrostic. This piyyuṭ is for a bar mitsvah, where a boy turns thirteen. ",
    "content": "<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\nA shiv&#8217;ata is a sevenfold blessing inserted into the Musaf service on Shabbat. This shiv&#8217;ata was written for use at a bar mitsvah. Each stanza begins with an example of thirteen as used in our tradition, followed by an alphabetical acrostic. This piyyuṭ is for a bar mitsvah, where a boy turns thirteen. The author is working on a piyyuṭ for a bat mitsvah, when a girl turns twelve, and when it is completed it will be linked here.\n</div>\n<hr />\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Hebrew)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Translation (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשְׁלֹשׁ עֶשְׂרֵה בְּרִיתוֹת <span class=\"acrostic\">אָ</span>ב הָמוֹן קִבֵּל עַל־בָּנִים<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">בְּ</span>רִית מִילָה גִּיל תּוֹרָה וּשְׂשׂוֹן חֲתָנִים<br />\nבְּיוֹם בַּר מִצְוָתוֹ <span class=\"acrostic\">גּ</span>וֹנֵן שׁוֹמְרֵי אֱמוּנִים<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">דּ</span>וֹר שָׁמוּר יִגְדַּל תַּֽחַת מָגִנִּים׃<br />\nבא״י מָגֵן אַבְרָהָם׃<br />\nאַתָּה גִּבּוֹר…\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThirteen covenants<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Mishnah Nedarim 3:11. In Genesis 17. the word “covenant” appears thirteen times.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> the father of multitudes<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Abraham&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> accepted upon his children: <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\ncircumcision, the cheer of Torah, and the joy of marriage. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nOn this one’s bar mitsvah, shield, o <span class=\"divine-referent\">Guardian of Faith</span>, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nthe guarded generation; let it grow under shields. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nBlessed are You, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Cause</span>, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Shield of Abraham</span>.<br />\nYou are mighty…\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשְׁלֹשׁ עֶשְׂרֵה מִדּוֹת <span class=\"acrostic\">הָ</span>רַחֲמִים הוֹרֵֽיתָ לְמָשׁוּי מִמַּֽיִם<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">וְ</span>נִשְׁבַּֽעְתָּ שֶׁטַּל חֶֽסֶד תּוֹרִיד מִשָּׁמַֽיִם<br />\nבְּיוֹם בַּר מִצְוָתוֹ <span class=\"acrostic\">זְ</span>כֹר זָכָר זֶה כִּמְנַשֶּׁה וְאֶפְרַֽיִם<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">חַ</span>זְּקֵֽהוּ בְּטַלְלֵי אוֹר הַשָּׁמַֽיִם׃<br />\nבא״י מְחַיֵּה הַמֵּתִים׃<br />\n<span class=\"instruction\">אשכנז</span> נַעֲרִיצְךָ/ <span class=\"instruction\">ספרד</span> כֶּֽתֶר…\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThirteen attributes of compassion<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Exodus 34:6-7&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> You taught to the one<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Moses&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> drawn from water, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nand You swore that gracious dew You would precipitate from heaven. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nOn this one’s bar mitsvah, remember this male like Menasseh and Ephraim.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> According to Genesis 48:20, the people Israel should be blessed by being compared to these two sons of Joseph.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nstrengthen him with dew of heavenly light! <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nBlessed are You, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Cause</span>, who revives the dead.<br />\n<span class=\"instruction\">Ashkenaz:</span> Let’s exult in You… <span class=\"instruction\">Sefarad:</span> A crown…\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשְׁלשָׁה עָשָׂר עִקָּרִים <span class=\"acrostic\">טְ</span>בוּעִים בְּדַת יִשְׂרָאֵל<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">יִ</span>גְדַּל אֱלֹהִים חַי וְיִשְׁתַּבַּח הַגּוֹאֵל<br />\nבְּיוֹם בַּר מִצְוָתוֹ <span class=\"acrostic\">כּ</span>וֹנְנֵֽהוּ לְמַלֵּא עֲשָׂרָה בַּאֲרִיאֵל<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">לְ</span>הוֹסִיף לִשְׁלֹֽשֶׁת קְדֻשּׁוֹת יִשְׂרָאֵל׃<br />\nבא״י הָאֵל (<span class=\"instruction\">שבת שובה –</span> הַמֶּֽלֶךְ)  הַקָּדוֹשׁ׃<br />\nתִּכַּֽנְתָּ…\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThirteen theses<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[6]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> First listed in Rambam’s commentary on Mishnah Sanhedrin 10:1, but brought into the post-service recitations as a “credo” of rabbinic Judaism, and rewritten in to the piyyuṭ Yigdal recited, in many communities, at the end of every Friday night service.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> are engraved in the law of Israel. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nMagnified and praised be <span class=\"divine-referent\">the living God</span>,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[7]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> The opening line from Yigdal&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> <span class=\"divine-referent\">the Redeemer</span>! <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nOn this one’s bar mitsvah, confirm him to fulfil ten<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_8');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_8');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[8]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_8\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Once reaching bar mitsvah age, a child can be counted in a minyan.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_8', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> in Ariel,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_9');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_9');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[9]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_9\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> A poetic term for Jerusalem, found in Isaiah 29:1&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_9', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nTo add to the three holinesses<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_10');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_10');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[10]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_10\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> &#8221;Three holinesses” refers to the threefold repetition of “holy” in Isaiah 6:3. And ten plus three is, of course, thirteen.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_10', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> of Israel! <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nBlessed are You, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Cause</span>, <span class=\"divine-referent\">the holy God</span> (<span class=\"instruction\">on Shabbat Shuva:</span> <span class=\"divine-referent\">Sovereign</span>)<br />\nYou established…\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשְׁלֹשׁ עֶשְׂרֵה מִדּוֹת <span class=\"acrostic\">מִ</span>לֵּל גְּדוֹל הַתַּנָּאִים<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">נִ</span>דְרֶֽשֶׁת הַתּוֹרָה בָּהֵן גַּם כִּתְבֵי מִקְרָאִים<br />\nבְּיוֹם בַּר מִצְוָתוֹ <span class=\"acrostic\">ס</span>וֹמֵךְ עָלֶֽיךָ הוּא וְכׇל־בָּאִים<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">עַ</span>ם שׁוֹמְרֵי שַׁבָּת וְעׇנְגָּהּ קוֹרְאִים׃<br />\nבא״י מְקַדֵּשׁ הַשַּׁבָּת׃<br />\nרְצֵה…\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThirteen principles<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_11');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_11');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_11\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[11]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_11\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> First listed in the opening of the Sifra, the thirteen hermeneutical principles of Rabbi Ishmael are recited every morning in traditional liturgies.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_11').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_11', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> spoke the greatest of the Tannaim,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_12');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_12');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_12\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[12]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_12\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Rabbi Ishmael ben Elisha&#8217;s system of halakhic exegesis became the norm by which all halakha was derived, and he was also an expert in aggadah. His school of students, Bei Rabbi Yishmael, brought down many important teachings. Only Rabbi Akiva reached his level of importance in his generation.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_12').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_12', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nby which the Torah is interpreted, as well as written scriptures. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nOn this one’s bar mitsvah, he relies on You — along with all comers, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nthe people keeping the sabbath and calling it a delight.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_13');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_13');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_13\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[13]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_13\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> See the Yism’ḥu text, recited as part of the sabbath service — in Ashkenaz practice exclusively as part of Musaf, and in Sephardi practice as part of every service.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_13').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_13', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nBlessed are You, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Cause</span>, who sanctifies the sabbath.<br />\nDesire…\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשְׁלשָׁה עָשָׂר שְׁעָרִים <span class=\"acrostic\">פִּ</span>תְחֵי הָעֲזָרָה<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">צַ</span>דִּיקִים הִשְׁתַּחֲווּ שָׁם בִּגְבוּרָה<br />\nבְּיוֹם בַּר מִצְוָתוֹ <span class=\"acrostic\">קִ</span>בֵּל עוֹל וְאוֹר הַתּוֹרָה<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">רְ</span>צֵה בְּתִפְלָתֵֽנוּ נַעֲבׇדְךָ בְּיִרְאָה׃<br />\nבא״י הַמַּחֲזִיר שְׁכִינָתוֹ לְצִיּוֹן׃<br />\nמוֹדִים…\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThirteen gates,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_14');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_14');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_14\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[14]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_14\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Of the Temple courtyard, listed in M. Shekalim 6:3&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_14').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_14', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> openings of the Courtyard; <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nthe righteous bowed prostrate there in might. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nOn this one’s bar mitsvah, he has taken up the yoke and light of the Torah. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nDesire our prayers, and we will worship You in awe!<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_15');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_15');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_15\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[15]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_15\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> A line from the old Erets Yisrael conclusion of this prayer.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_15').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_15', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nBlessed are You, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Cause</span>, who returns <span class=\"divine-referent\">Their</span> presence to Ẓíōn.<br />\nWe thank…\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשְׁלֹשָׁה עָשָׂר שׁוֹפָרוֹת <span class=\"acrostic\">שֻׁ</span>לְחָנוֹת וְהִשְׁתַּחֲוָיוֹת כָּנֶגְדָם<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">שֶׁ</span>כֵּן נִמְסְרָה לָנוּ מָסוֹרָתֵֽנוּ עַל־יָדָם<br />\nבְּיוֹם בַּר מִצְוָתוֹ <span class=\"acrostic\">תּ</span>וֹלֶה בְּךָ כׇּל־אָדָם<br />\n<span class=\"acrostic\">תּ</span>וֹדוֹת נוֹדֶה וּלְךָ נִסְגֹּד צוּרָם וִיסוֹדָם׃<br />\nבא״י הַטּוֹב שִׁמְךָ וּלְךָ נָאֶה לְהוֹדוֹת׃<br />\nשִׂים…\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThirteen shofars, tables, and prostrations corresponding,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_16');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_16');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_16\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[16]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_16\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> See Mishnah Shekalim 6:1&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_16').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_16', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nas such our tradition was passed on to us by their hand. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nOn this one’s bar mitsvah, every human relies on You. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nThanks we thank, and to You we bow, their <span class=\"divine-referent\">Rock</span> and <span class=\"divine-referent\">Foundation</span>! <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nBlessed are You, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Cause</span>, whose name is good, to You it is pleasing to praise.<br />\nGrant…\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשְׁלֹשָׁה עָשָׂר שָׁנִים יְׄלִידֵי צִׄיּוֹן מַגִּיעִים לַבַּגְרוּת<br />\nחֲׄכָמִים קְׄבָעֽוּהוּ עַל־לוּחוֹת חָרוּת<br />\nבְּיוֹם בַּר מִצְוָתוֹ מְׄנָת אֵׄל כְּאַבְרָהָם וְרוּת<br />\nיְׄקַבֵּל רֵׄעֲךָ הַזֶּה שָׁלוֹם וְשַׁלְוָה וְחֵרוּת׃<br />\nבא״י הַמְבָרֵךְ אֶת־עַמּוֹ יִשְׂרָאֵל בַּשָּׁלוֹם׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThirteen years Ẓíōn’s children arrive to adulthood.<br />\nThe righteous established it, engraved on tablets.<br />\nOn this one’s bar mitsvah, the divine portion of Abraham and Ruth<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_17');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_17');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_17\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[17]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_17\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Both of whom accepted the Torah by their own choice, rather than having been obligated into it since birth.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_17').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_17', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nthis friend of Yours will accept, peace, satistfaction, and freedom!<br />\nBlessed are You, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Cause</span>, who blesses <span class=\"divine-referent\">Their</span> people Israel in peace.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\">Notes</span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" style=\"display: none;; display: none;\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\"></span></p></div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container__1\" style=\"\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">Notes</caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >1</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Mishnah Nedarim 3:11. In Genesis 17. the word “covenant” appears thirteen times.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >2</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Abraham</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >3</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Exodus 34:6-7</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >4</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Moses</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >5</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">According to Genesis 48:20, the people Israel should be blessed by being compared to these two sons of Joseph.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >6</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">First listed in Rambam’s commentary on Mishnah Sanhedrin 10:1, but brought into the post-service recitations as a “credo” of rabbinic Judaism, and rewritten in to the piyyuṭ Yigdal recited, in many communities, at the end of every Friday night service.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >7</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">The opening line from Yigdal</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_8\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >8</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Once reaching bar mitsvah age, a child can be counted in a minyan.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_9\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >9</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">A poetic term for Jerusalem, found in Isaiah 29:1</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_10\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >10</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">&#8221;Three holinesses” refers to the threefold repetition of “holy” in Isaiah 6:3. And ten plus three is, of course, thirteen.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_11\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_11');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >11</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">First listed in the opening of the Sifra, the thirteen hermeneutical principles of Rabbi Ishmael are recited every morning in traditional liturgies.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_12\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_12');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >12</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Rabbi Ishmael ben Elisha&#8217;s system of halakhic exegesis became the norm by which all halakha was derived, and he was also an expert in aggadah. His school of students, Bei Rabbi Yishmael, brought down many important teachings. Only Rabbi Akiva reached his level of importance in his generation.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_13\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_13');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >13</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">See the Yism’ḥu text, recited as part of the sabbath service — in Ashkenaz practice exclusively as part of Musaf, and in Sephardi practice as part of every service.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_14\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_14');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >14</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Of the Temple courtyard, listed in M. Shekalim 6:3</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_15\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_15');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >15</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">A line from the old Erets Yisrael conclusion of this prayer.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_16\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_16');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >16</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">See Mishnah Shekalim 6:1</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_17\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_17');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >17</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Both of whom accepted the Torah by their own choice, rather than having been obligated into it since birth.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n </tbody> </table> </div></div><script type=\"text/javascript\"> function footnote_expand_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').show(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('−'); } function footnote_collapse_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').hide(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('+'); } function footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1() { if (jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').is(':hidden')) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); } else { footnote_collapse_reference_container__1(); } } function footnote_moveToReference__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } } function footnote_moveToAnchor__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } }</script>",
